{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κάλως</b> [ᾰ], ὁ, <br /> <i>genitive</i> κάλω, <i>accusative</i> κάλων: <i>Epic dialect</i> and <i>Ionic dialect</i> <u><b>κάλος</u></b>, ου, ὁ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.260, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.36, also 4th c.BC: Aeneas Tacticus 11.6 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Attic dialect</i> Inscrr. have <i>nominative</i> dual κάλω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.330.19, _nominative_ (and _accusative_ ?) _plural_ κάλως [prev. work]22.1610.13, 1611.57, 1612.68: as _nominative_ _sing._ (?) [prev. work]1673.18;\">Refs</a>] late <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>nominative</i> <i>plural</i> κάλωες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 2.725; _accusative_ κάλωας 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Argonautica” 255, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 2.223; _dative_ κάλωσι 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Argonautica” 239 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:—<b>reefing rope, reef</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” [same place]; τῶν ἱστίων τοὺς κάλους 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.36 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], cf. Aen.Tact.[same place]; κάλως ἐξῑέναι let out <b>the reefs</b>, i.e. <b>set sail</b>, ὅταν στράτευμ᾽ Αργεῖον ἐξιῇ κάλως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 94 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐχθροὶ γὰρ ἐξιᾶσι πάντα δὴ κάλων are letting out every <b>reef</b>, i.e. using every effort, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Med.” 278, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 756 (and Scholia (at [prev. work])); τοὺς κάλως ἔκλυε καὶ Χάλα πόδα 4th c.BC: Epicrates Comicus 10.5; πάνγας ἔσεισε κάλους “Anthologia Graeca” 9.545 (1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Crinagoras Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φόνιον ἐξίει κάλων let murder <b>loose</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 837; πάντα κάλων ἐκτείναντα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 338a; ἐφέντες [prev. author] “Sis.” 389c; κινεῖν 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Scyth.” 11; γαστρὶ πάντας ἐπιτρωπῶσι κάλωας 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 2.223; κάλων τείνας οὔριον εὐφροσυνᾶν “IG” 14.793.8 (from Naples). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>rope, line</b>, κάλον (variant{-ων}) κατεῖναι let down <b>a sounding-line</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.28 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ κάλω παραπλεῖν to be towed along shore, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cable</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.96 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρυμνήτης κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 770 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ ἐπὶ τῶν κ. βαίνοντες tight-<b>rope</b> walkers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Rh.Pr.” 9. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7785","accentedUnicode":"κάλος","shortDef":"rope","mediumDef":"rope","stepGloss":"rope","stepTransliteration":"kalos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}